[00:08.32]I wore my story on my skin
[00:11.61]Every mark where sin had been
[00:14.90]Ink and memories intertwined
[00:18.18]A former heart, a former mind
[00:21.47]I didn’t ask the Father’s will
[00:24.75]I only chased what I thought felt real
[00:28.04]These markings spoke of who I was
[00:31.33]Before I knew redeeming love
[00:34.61]Now I read Your Word and I understand
[00:37.90]This body was always in Your hands
[00:41.18]A living temple, bought with blood
[00:44.47]Not mine to boast, but Yours, O God
[00:47.75]These tattoos on my body
[00:51.04]They don’t define my soul
[00:54.33]They tell the story of a man
[00:57.61]Before You made me whole
[01:00.90]If I could wash them off so
[01:04.18]I’d let the old man go
[01:07.47]They remind me who I was
[01:10.76]Not who I am in You, my Lord
[01:14.04]I don’t display them, I don’t brag
[01:17.33]I keep them covered, I won’t drag
[01:20.61]The old identity back to life
[01:23.90]That died with You that night
[01:27.18]Your mercy runs much deeper still
[01:30.47]Than every needle, every thrill
[01:33.76]My flesh may wear the former name
[01:37.04]But my spirit bears Yours, unashamed
[01:40.33]You said my life would bring You praise
[01:43.61]Not marked by pride, but holy ways
[01:46.90]So now I glorify You, God
[01:50.19]With every breath, with every thought
[01:53.47]These tattoos on my body
[01:56.76]They don’t define my soul
[02:00.04]They tell the story of a man
[02:03.33]Before You made me whole
[02:06.61]If I could wash them off so
[02:09.90]I’d let the old man go
[02:13.19]They remind me who I was
[02:16.47]Not who I am in You, my Lord
[02:19.76]Crucified with Christ, I live no more
[02:23.04]Your Spirit wrote a better law
[02:26.33]Not on my skin, but on my heart
[02:29.62]Where truth and grace now leave their mark
[02:32.90]I am not bound by former sin
[02:36.19]I’m clothed in Christ, made new within
[02:39.47]These tattoos on my body
[02:42.76]Are fading day by day
[02:46.05]But what You’ve done inside of me
[02:49.33]Will never pass away
[02:52.62]My life proclaims Your holiness
[02:55.90]My heart, Your dwelling place
[02:59.19]I may wear marks of yesterday
[03:02.47]But today I live for Your great name
[03:05.76]So let my life be living proof
[03:09.05]Not ink or flesh, but gospel truth
[03:12.33]I am redeemed, forever free
[03:15.62]Your glory written over me
